org.apache.felix.ipojo.extender.queue

Interface QueueListener

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ReplayQueueEventProxy

    public interface QueueListener
    A QueueListener provides queue management information to external entities:
    • Job submission
    • Job execution
    • Job result (success or failure)
    Implementer of this interface should not block as the invocation is done synchronously. Implementers are responsible to register themselves in the QueueService they'll observe.

    • Method Detail

      • enlisted

        void enlisted(JobInfo info)
        Invoked when a job is just being enlisted (before processing). Only JobInfo.getEnlistmentTime() and JobInfo.getWaitDuration() provides meaningful values. Note that waitDuration value is re-evaluated at each call.
        Parameters:
        info - The job being enlisted

      • started

        void started(JobInfo info)
        Invoked when a job's execution is just about to be started. Only JobInfo.getEnlistmentTime(), JobInfo.getWaitDuration(), JobInfo.getStartTime() and JobInfo.getExecutionDuration() provides meaningful values. Note that executionDuration value is re-evaluated at each call.
        Parameters:
        info - The job being started

      • executed

        void executed(JobInfo info,
            Object result)
        Invoked when a job's execution is finished successfully. Note the implementers should not retain any references to the provided result (memory leak).
        Parameters:
        info - The executed job
        result - The job's result

      • failed

        void failed(JobInfo info,
          Throwable throwable)
        Invoked when a job's execution is finished with error. Note the implementers should not retain any references to the provided throwable (memory leak).
        Parameters:
        info - The failed job
        throwable - The job's thrown exception
